{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ghost}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Yamask}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ghost|prevnum=561|prev=Sigilyph|nextnum=563|next=Cofagrigus|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Yamask}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Yamask\n|jname=デスマス\n|tmname=Desumasu\n|category=Spirit\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Ghost\n|abilityn=1\n|abilitylayout=1\n|ability1=Mummy\n|ndex=562\n|udex=068\n|u2dex=124\n|height-ftin=1\'08"\n|height-m=0.5\n|weight-lbs=3.3\n|weight-kg=1.5\n|egggroupn=2\n|egggroup1=Mineral\n|egggroup2=Amorphous\n|eggcycles=25\n|expyield=61\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Black\n|catchrate=190\n|evtotal=1\n|evde=1\n|body=04\n|pokefordex=yamask\n|generation=5\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Yamask\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'デスマス\'\'\' \'\'Desumasu\'\') is a {{type|Ghost}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Cofagrigus}} starting at [[level]] 34.\n\nIn [[Galar]], Yamask has a [[regional variant]] that is {{2t|Ground|Ghost}}. It evolves into {{p|Runerigus}}.\n\n==Biology==\n[[File:Yamask mask.png|left|thumb|200px|The mask of a Yamask]]\nYamask is a shadow-like Pokémon holding a mask that has a face from its time as a [[human]]. It has two shadowy, tendril-like arms and large, red eyes. It also has a small tail-like appendage that holds the mask.\n\nDue to being a human long ago, it has memories of being a human. If someone wears the mask Yamask carries, they will become possessed by the Yamask in question. Sometimes, it looks at this mask and cries, apparently in longing. Yamask is known to wander the ruins of ancient civilizations.\n{{left clear}}\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Yamask anime.png|250px|thumb|left|Yamask in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[James\'s Yamask]]====\nA Yamask appeared before {{TRT}} in \'\'[[BW023|Battling For The Love of Bug-Types!]]\'\', and [[James]] was able to {{pkmn2|caught|catch}} him. At the end of the {{series|Best Wishes}}, James had to give Yamask to {{an|Giovanni}} as a sign that they accomplished something in [[Unova]].\n\n====Other====\nYamask debuted in \'\'[[BW014|A Night in the Nacrene City Museum!]]\'\', where it was causing havoc in the [[Nacrene City]] Museum. This eventually turned out to be because Yamask\'s mask had been put on display after it accidentally dropped it while sleeping. In the end, [[Lenora]], along with {{Ash}}, {{an|Iris}}, {{an|Cilan}}, and [[Hawes]] gained an understanding with it and gave its mask back. Yamask then left the museum peacefully.\n\n===Minor appearances===\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW014|Yamask|Ash\'s Pokédex|Yamask, the Spirit Pokémon. Yamask is a {{type|Ghost}} Pokémon that wanders the ruins of ancient civilizations.}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW037|Yamask|Ash\'s Pokédex|Yamask, the Spirit Pokémon. A Ghost-type Pokémon, Yamask wanders the ruins of ancient civilizations.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:BW Agency Yamask Vanillite Solosis.png|thumb|150px|Yamask in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nA Yamask takes part in [[BW Agency]]\'s roster. It {{pkmn|training|trained}} along with a {{p|Solosis}}, a {{p|Vanillite}}, and [[Gigi]] for the [[Pokémon Musical]] in \'\'[[PS482|To Make a Musical]]\'\'.\n\nA Yamask appeared in \'\'[[PS479|The Case of the Missing Pokémon]]\'\', where it was one of the Pokémon kidnapped by [[Team Plasma]]. It was later returned to its {{pkmn|Trainer}} after being found in a stronghold.\n\nA Yamask appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[PS536|Cold Storage Battle]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Yamask (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=ghost}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=V|reg1=Unova|num1=068|label1={{gameabbrev5|BW}}:|reg2=Unova|num2=124|label2={{gameabbrev5|B2W2}}:}}\n{{Dex/